    .page.first-page
      .container.text-center
        img(src="img/Logo.svg", alt="OneDB")
        h1(style="display: none") OneDB
        h2 Connect your frontend to the cloud. For free, forever.
        p.
          OneDB is an open source, decentralized backend - it handles user authentication,
          data storage, and validation, so <b>you can focus on creating a beautiful user interface</b>.
        p.
          Anyone can host a OneDB instance, and end-users can decide where they want to store their data.
          This means <b>end-users have complete control and ownership</b> over their data. And by utilizing the existing network of OneDB instances, you can <b>deploy your app for free</b>, forever.
        .text-center.cta-buttons
          a.float-md-left.mr-3.btn.btn-lg.btn-primary(href="https://medium.com/@bbrennan/onedb-build-cloud-enabled-apps-with-zero-cost-bc3cc7ff86e6") Read the announcement
          a.float-md-right.btn.btn-lg.btn-primary(href="https://docs.one-db.org") View the docs
    .page.page-inverse
      .container-fluid.features
        .row
          .col-12.col-lg-4
            h3 Infinite Scale
            ul
              li
                .icon
                  i.fa.fa-cloud
                span Develop and deploy cloud-enabled apps without worrying about backend infrastructure
              li
                .icon
                  i.fa.fa-database
                span Data validation and storage are handled by the growing network of OneDB instances
              li
                .icon
                  i.fa.fa-users
                span Users can log in, save their data, and share it with other users in the OneDB network
          .col-12.col-lg-4
            h3 Zero Cost
            ul
              li
                .icon
                  i.fa.fa-money-bill
                span Deploying an app with OneDB is free for developers, forever, at any scale
              li
                .icon
                  i.fa.fa-server
                span Each instance in the network is responsible for paying its own infrastructure costs
              li
                .icon
                  i.fa.fa-hand-holding-usd
                span The instance at <code>one-db.datafire.io</code> allows up to 10MB of free storage per user
          .col-12.col-lg-4
            h3 Data Liberation
            ul
              li
                .icon
                  i.fa.fa-dove
                span OneDB gives users complete ownership of their data
              li
                .icon
                  i.fa.fa-hdd
                span Users can store data on their hard drive, inside their company's intranet, or on a cloud provider
              li
                .icon
                  i.fa.fa-lock
                span Fine-grained permissions give users complete control over their data
    .page.sample-code-page
      .container
        h2.text-center Powerful Tools with a Simple Interface
        p.
          OneDB makes it easy to add user authentication, data storage, and validation to your frontend.
          Check out <a href="https://docs.one-db.org">the documentation</a> to learn more.
        script(src="https://gist.github.com/bobby-brennan/b962069ee7a5e79e26d04f85872393ae.js")
    .page.page-inverse.team-page
      .container
        h2.text-center Meet the OneDB Team
        mixin teammate(name, description)
          .teammate.text-center
            h4.text-capitalize.text-center= name
            img(src="/img/team/" + name + (name === 'bob' ? '.png' : '.jpg'))
            p.text-left= description
        .row
          .col
            +teammate('bobby', 'Bobby Brennan is the lead developer for OneDB. He has spent the last four years building backend developer tools at DataFire, maintains a number of open source projects, and previously worked for Google as a Senior Software Engineer')
          //.col
            +teammate('joe', 'Joe Pelletier is an experienced product leader with expertise in growing and managing successful enterprise SaaS platforms. Joe is currently a Director of Product Management at Veracode, where he focuses on early stage product development, incubation, and product portfolio strategy.')
          .col
            +teammate('andrew', 'Andrew Brennan has extensive experience in the software industry, particularly in product management, sales, and marketing. He currently works at DataFire, and was previously at InsightSquared.')
        .row
          .col
            +teammate('throop', 'Throop Wilder has co-founded and built successful startups in computer software, networking hardware, and energy storage. Throop co-founded American Internet (sold to Cisco Systems) and Crossbeam Systems (sold to Blue Coat / Symantec). He later founded and ran 24m Technologies, a manufacturer of ultra-low cost lithium-ion batteries.')
          .col
            +teammate('bob', 'Bob Brennan has built and run several software companies throughout his career. He recently retired as CEO of Veracode, which was sold to CA Technologies in April, 2017. Prior to Veracode, Bob served as CEO of Iron Mountain, which had acquired his previous company, Connected Corporation')
